{
  "texts": [
    "DistTGL [75] incorporates an additional static node memory within the dynamic GNNs, which not only enhances the model's accuracy but also accelerates its convergence rate.",
    "Two novel training methodologies, namely time period parallelism and memory parallelism, are also proposed.",
    "These two methodologies enable capturing a comparable number of graph event dependencies on multiple GPUs, similar to that achieved in single GPU training.",
    "Prefetching and pipelining techniques are utilized to mitigate the associated costs of batch formation and to facilitate overlap with GPU training.",
    "The DistTGL [75] framework offers notable enhancements in terms of convergence speed and training throughput compared to TGL [74]."
  ]
}